 :tx/rationale "ASSESSMENT FINDING: Concept Collapse Root Cause — Emergent concepts collapsing to single cluster. Root cause: JOIN_THRESHOLD = 0.20 with HashEmbedder. The HashEmbedder produces embeddings via BLAKE3 word hashing — deterministic but purely word-overlap based. In a project where most observations share vocabulary (store, entity, spec, implementation, convergence), all observations exceed 0.20 cosine similarity. The agglomerative clustering merges all high-similarity pairs, eventually collapsing to 1 mega-cluster. Evidence: no test prevents single-concept collapse; test crystallize_three_similar_observations only checks at least 1 concept formed. This is a measurement problem, not a conceptual one — observations genuinely contain distinct concepts but the embedding cannot distinguish semantic domains sharing vocabulary. Solution: replace HashEmbedder with TF-IDF weighted embeddings using store vocabulary statistics. IDF computed from the store's own attribute/value corpus downweights common terms (store, entity) and surfaces distinguishing terms. No external ML dependency needed. Alternative: raise JOIN_THRESHOLD to 0.35-0.45 (quick fix but breaks detection of genuinely similar observations). Better: TF-IDF + entropy regularization in crystallization + maximum cluster size cap. VERIFICATION: After TF-IDF implementation, run concept clustering on current 130+ observations. Should produce 5-15 distinct concepts instead of 1-3. DOGFOOD-2 concept quality should improve from baseline. INTERACTS WITH: OBSERVER-6 (ontology discovery blocked by collapse), DOGFOOD-2 score (hash embedder identified as bottleneck), seed assembly (concept-aware seeding depends on meaningful concepts). TRACES TO: OBSERVER-6 (ontology discovery loop), INV-CONCEPT-001."
